,Not Recommended,541100,27371136,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,GiraffeMystic,"Game has no way to adjust keybindings that I'm aware of and the controls themselves feel messy and clunky. The overall lighting is aweful and it takes forever to find a toy plane hiden in an obscure spot. Way too dark with no way to adjust the lighting.  Keybinds where c for crouch, e for action, and w-a-s-d for movement. Mouse for looking/ view. Although it sounds simple enough, it bothered me enough to mention it.The overall design of the levels/ areas seem laughable. You start out with an oddly designed, but rather nice looking house and then from there it just goes downhill. I say this because you seem to spend the vast majority of the game wandering the house and the house is just so ridiuclous. The basement desgin is so ridiculous that if it was real I would first facepalm, and then suggest moving in homeless people to live there because of how unecessarily large and maze like it is. This house designer is cray-cray no joke.As for Krampus the monster, he feels uneventful and not scarey. I'll get bored wandering around lost in the dark before he shows up and then when he'll show up randomly its just like ""oh, hi there Krampy"". First few times felt jump-scare like, but its only jump scares and those lose effect after a few times of it being repeated. His image itself was not at all scarey, in real life maybe, but a game? Nope. I've had better jumpscares from Slendy (SlenderMan) to be quite honest, and he's super underated.Lots of run around pick up a key then run around some more to find another key and then another and so on. This gameplay got repetitive and boring very fast. Theres a few other puzzle types, but the bit with the keys felt very heavy. I stayed playing for the story.Story seems to be alright, but I only just made it to the attic stairs when my entire game crashed. Which was a bit of a buzzkill, even after being frustrated with the very poor lighting and annoying key binds. I'm now stuck in the attic, mkay.TLDR:No tutorial, so good luck learning the keys and what to do.Poor key bindings and no options or way to adjust any part of the game be it lighting or key binds.The lighting is terrible and theres no way to brighten the game to look for objects/ objectives, which are, by the way hidden in obscure and dark little nooks and cranies.The gameplay is repetative. Its basically find a key and find a lock for said key, then continue to find more keys and more locks after some point. Lots of find said object and goto said location with said object.Areas are designed in weird and crazy ways which don't make any sense to me.Cheap jumpscares that even Slenderman can do better.Maybe worth a shot if on sale or cheap in general, but the lighting and key binds need improvement, as for the jumpscares, well have you ever played Spooky's House of JumpScares? Yea, and it almost feels kinda rushed in some aspects. Is it just me or is this game super short and relatively easy? The game isn't very bad, but its not very good either."
