76561198048974498,Recommended,541100,26131362,"Posted: 20 October, 2016",all,rjmacready,"No options. Constant crashes. Infrequent saves. Long load screens. A completely lame ending. So why am I thumbing this♥♥♥♥♥♥up, exactly?Well, it is kinda creepy. Which a horror game should be. And it delivers the occasional effective ""jump scare"" which, no matter how much people like to belittle them, actually take some skill to execute correctly. It also has one halfway-decent ""puzzle"" idea, and a couple of other ""puzzles"" which at least aspire to a challenge greater than opening a cupboard and finding a key inside (though there's plenty of that, too).Oh, and when you press the keys on a piano, instead of the requisite piano sample we all know and love from other first-person games, you get a blatant plinky-plonky ELECTRONIC KEYBOARD sound instead. And that's just sheer genius in my book.Look, it's no kinda masterpiece, and five bucks really is taking the♥♥♥♥♥♥for a cheap♥♥♥♥♥♥indie game that lasts barely thirty minutes (maybe a smidgen over, if you crash frequently enough). Only buy if you're hard-up for a horror game and it's on sale for less than a buck (so maybe wait for the Christmas, rather than Halloween, sale). Done deal.Verdict: 5.5/10 (the extra .5 being for the plonky synth sound. GENIUS, I tell you)!"
